GenerateMethods.Name: Highest Projected
GenerateMethods.Description: Generates lineups with the highest number of projected points.

GenerateMethods.Name: High Leverage
GenerateMethods.Description: Optimizes lineups with the highest leverage players to follow low owned high scoring players. *Tournaments*

GenerateMethods.Name: High Safety
GenerateMethods.Description: Optimizes lineups with the highest owned players to follow the field. *Double-Ups*

GenerateMethods.Name: Tournament - GPP
GenerateMethods.Description: This model favors high leverage players with high ceilings. Lineups will have lower ownership for high risk and reward.

GenerateMethods.Name: Double Ups
GenerateMethods.Description: This model favors higher owned players. Lineups will have higher ownership which will follow the crowd.

GenerateMethods.Name: Daily Matchup
GenerateMethods.Description: More heavily favors players with the best matchups based on our Matchups page.

GenerateMethods.Name: Usage
GenerateMethods.Description: Optimizes lineups for the highest combined usage from players in the lineup.

GenerateMethods.Name: Predictable & Consistent
GenerateMethods.Description: Places more value on players who have been predictable. *Double-Ups*

GenerateMethods.Name: High Ceiling
GenerateMethods.Description: Fills lineups with players that have shown the ability to score big. This is a riskier option but can pay off. *Tournaments*

GenerateMethods.Name: High Floor
GenerateMethods.Description: Fills lineups with players that don't score low.

GenerateMethods.Name: Boom Bust Random
GenerateMethods.Description: Optimizes lineups that will randomly give players their ceiling or floor scores.

GenerateMethods.Name: Stars and Scrubs
GenerateMethods.Description: Fills the lineups with as many high salary studs as possible. *Tournaments*

GenerateMethods.Name: Points Per Game
GenerateMethods.Description: Use PPG value from daily site in place of our projections.

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Select the number of lineups you want generated.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Lineup Count

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Max Exposure limits the number of times a player will be included in a lineup set. At 70% Max Exposure, with 10 lineups a player will be in at most 7 lineups.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Max Exposure

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Set the max exposure limit per position. This takes priority over the standard exposure if a position matches.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Position Exposure

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Your liked Players can exceed the Max Exposure value.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Liked Exposure

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Set the maxmium total projected ownership you want for optimized lineups.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Lineup pOwn% Max

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Projected Individual Ownership Range for players to be used when optimizing lineups.
AdvancedOptions.Name: pOwn% Range

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Your liked players will recieve a projection boost while optimizing lineups. Higher projections will generally include those players in more lineups.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Liked Projection Boost

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Your liked players become your player pool. IMPORTANT: Make sure you have enough players liked to cover every position and your exposure settings otherwise lineups can't be built.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Liked Player Pool

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Use the industry consensus projection (if available) instead of the LineStar projection.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Use Consensus Projection

AdvancedOptions.Desc: If you adjust a projection for a player who is ruled out, by default they will not be included in optimized lineups. Unless that is what you want.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Always use adjusted projection

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Enable this option to exclude any player with a injury status.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Exclude Injured Players

AdvancedOptions.Desc: If possible flex late night players to flex positions.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Flex Late Players

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Set the maximum number of players per team you want included in your lineup.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Max Players Per Team

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Enable this option if you only want Starting players to be included in your lineups.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Starters Only

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Treats the top 10 liked players by the LineStar community as if you liked them.
AdvancedOptions.Name: FanSense (Top 10 Liked)

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Treats the top 10 excluded players by the LineStar community as as if you excluded them.
AdvancedOptions.Name: FanSense (Top 10 Excluded)

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Set the minimum salary threshold. Players below this salary value will not be used when generating lineups.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Minimum Salary

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Set the minimum projection threshold. Players below this projection value will not be used when generating lineups.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Minimum Projection

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Variance is essentially projection grouping, players who are projected closely are grouped to the same projection. Higher Variance increases projection grouping size.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Variance

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Adds 0-100% randomness to each players projection. IE. 5% will adjust a players projection +-0-5% from their base projection. Every optimization is different.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Randomness

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Set the variance level per position. This takes priority over the standard variance if a position matches.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Position Variance

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Set the minimum salary budget to be used when generating lineups. Lineups will not be generated using less salary than the value specified.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Min Budget Use

AdvancedOptions.Desc: Sets the maximum salary budget to be used when generating lineups. Lineups will not be generated using more salary than the value specified.
AdvancedOptions.Name: Max Budget Use

StackingOptions.Desc: Include this many offensive players from the opposing team when this stack is used.
StackingOptions.Name: Game Stack

StackingOptions.Desc: Players between these salary values can be included in the stack
StackingOptions.Name: Player Salary Range

StackingOptions.Desc: Players between these projections values can be used stacks.
StackingOptions.Name: Projection Range For Players

StackingOptions.Desc: Projected Ownership Range for players included in the stack.
StackingOptions.Name: Projected Ownership Range

StackingOptions.Desc: When a team is stacked, ensure the final optimizations don't include another player from this team.
StackingOptions.Name: Limit Team To Stack
